import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    sns.set_palette("husl")
    chart = sns.barplot(x='year', y='net_generation', hue='source', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['source'])['net_generation'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='source', y='net_generation', data=data)
    chart.axhline(data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Average: {data['net_generation'].mean():.2f}")
    chart.set(xlabel='Source', ylabel='Average Net Generation')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation')
    sns.heatmap(data, cmap='YlGnBu')
    plt.title('What is the total net generation by year and source?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
